description: From Middle English misheren, from Old English mishȳran, mishīeran (“to hear amiss, not listen to, disobey”), equivalent to mis- +‎ hear.

verbs.description: mishear (third-person singular simple present mishears, present participle mishearing, simple past and past participle misheard)

examples: I misheard when she asked for mints, and gave her mince instead.
